Cocoa Cinnamon Lip Balm (Warm Brown Tint ~15ml)
Ingredients:
	•	2 tsp beeswax
	•	2 tsp shea butter
	•	2 tsp coconut oil
	•	½ tsp cocoa powder (for a brown tint)
	•	⅛ tsp cinnamon powder - for warmth and plumping(optional)
	•	2 drops vitamin E

Instructions:
	1.	Melt beeswax, shea butter, and coconut oil in a double boiler.
	2.	Stir in cocoa powder and cinnamon powder until smooth.
	3.	Remove from heat, add vitamin E, and mix well.
	4.	Pour into a container and let cool for about 30–45 minutes.

Shelf Life: 6–9 months
Tint: Warm brown with a soft sheen.
Increase cocoa powder for deeper color 

Simple and all natural diy plumping tinted lip balm in warm brown with a soft sheen.
